    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2010-03-25</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2011-01-20T16:54:23Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends federal patent law to revise the authorization of civil suits to collect one-half of the $500 penalty for false marking.</p> <p>Limits the right to file a civil action in a U.S. district court to persons who have suffered a competitive injury as a result of a violation of the prohibition against false marking. (Thus repeals the right of any person to sue for the penalty.) Allows a person who has suffered a competitive injury to file a civil action to recover damages adequate to compensate for the injury. (Current law allows any person to collect up to one-half of $500 for every such offense.)</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend title 35, United States Code, to provide recourse under the patent law for persons who suffer competitive injury as a result of false markings.</title>
